<statement>
<p>Solve this system of equations using elimination.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{3}{x}-{6}{y}=-{48}</m> </p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{5}{x}+{3}{y}={37}</m></p>
<p><input type="text" style="width:10.6ch" name="qn0" id="qn0" value="" autocomplete="off" aria-label="Question 1" class="text"/></p>

</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li><m>\displaystyle{\left({2},{9}\right)}</m></li></ul></p><p>We chose (for no special reason) to use the first equation to eliminate x from the second equation.</p>
<p>To eliminate we need the scaled version of equation one to have a coefficient of -5. So we scale by <m>\displaystyle-\frac{{5}}{{3}}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-\frac{{{5}}}{{3}}{\left({3}{x}+-{6}{y}\right)}=-\frac{{{5}}}{{3}}{\left(-{48}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{\left({5}\right)}{x}+{10}{y}={80}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{5}{x}+{3}{y}={37}</m></p>
<p>Adding these two equations gives us</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{13}{y}={117}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=\frac{{117}}{{13}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}={9}</m></p>
<p>Finally we can substitute this y value into the first equation to solve for x.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{3}{x}+-{6}{\left({9}\right)}=-{48}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{3}{x}+{\left(-{54}\right)}=-{48}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{3}{x}=-{48}-{\left(-{54}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{3}{x}={6}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=\frac{{6}}{{3}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}={2}</m></p>
<p>Thus the answer is <m>\displaystyle{\left({2},{9}\right)}</m>.</p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>